question: Can midostaurin inhibit angiogenesis?
ideal_answer: Yes, midostaurin can inhibit angiogenesis through the inhibition of ithe vascular endothelial growth factor receptor.

snippets.text: Midostaurin was a prototype kinase inhibitor, originally developed as a protein kinase C inhibitor and subsequently as an angiogenesis inhibitor, based on its inhibition of vascular endothelial growth factor receptor.
